title: Which musical instrument name ends with 'O'? - Quora

response.answer_text: Kazoo, hosho (African/Zimbabwean rattle), banjo, cello, bajo sexto, didgeridoo, gandigan a kayo (Philippine xylophone), marimbao (string instrument from Brazil), piano, piccolo (flute), theorbo (type of lute) cuatro (Latin American lute) dobro, bongo (drum), mandocello, daiko/taiko (Japanese drum), cimbasso (brass instrument), xiao (Chinese flute), yun lo (Chinese gong type), ahoko (African/Ivory Coast rattle), bombardino (Spanish euphonium), clavicembalo or jus cembalo (Italian pianoforte/harpsichord), guiro (rhythm instrument), komungo (Korean zither), sampho (Cambodian drum), soprillo (small piccolo saxophone), zufalo (Italian flute).
Jell-O. What, you don’t know how to make music with jell-O?
